const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Base title="The Practice" description="What Miracle of Mind is: a free 7-minute guided meditation of breath and attention.">
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow">The action layer</p>
    <h1>The Practice: Miracle of Mind</h1>
    <p class="lede">Miracle of Mind is a free, guided meditation you can do in about seven minutes a day. It works with breath and attention — the family of practices much of the research on this site examines.</p>
    <h3>The 7-minute structure</h3>
    <p>The practice combines a short breath-based process with a period of directed attention, designed to be simple enough to do daily without instruction beyond the guided audio. It asks for no belief, posture equipment, or prior experience.</p>
    <h3>How to start</h3>
    <p>The practice is offered through the free Miracle of Mind app. Begin with one session a day, ideally at the same time, for a couple of weeks — most of the research here studies effects over four to eight weeks of regular practice.</p>
    <div class="cta">
      <h3>Start the 7-minute practice</h3>
      <p style="color:#eef1ea">Free, guided, no experience needed.</p>
      <a href="https://miracleofmind.org/">Get Miracle of Mind →</a>
    </div>
    <p class="disclaimer">Meditation is not a treatment for any medical or psychological condition and does not replace professional care. If you live with a health condition, talk with a qualified professional about whether and how to add a practice.</p>
  </section>
</Base>
